The paper deals with low-level vision problems and proposes a new approach for image modeling using a learnable network architecture. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of optimization models and prior regularization, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces a new optimization process, which involves proximal gradient updating and adaptive averaging, indicating that it may be relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories.
